Have your camera charged and enough memory to store all those great pics of blue blue sky and red rock mountains. Really soft ice cream and unreasonably huge waffle cones. Eh. Not great.
Not terrible for chain pizza. But not really good either.

Great food like the NY location, with some different choices here like Okonomiyaki ($7) and a stranger version of the famous rice cakes - the Yunnanese version has tomatoes and goat cheese ($15).

Greatest hotel ever. The Momofuku suite of restaurants is located next door, there are TVs in the bathroom mirrors, and there is a big fitness center and a huge pool, with personal cabanas (I did get a special rate though).
One of those places where every bite of food is incredible. You can't go wrong, but you must definitely get the Patty Melt, which comes with amazing fries ($17).

Federal law changes IN October 2014 WILL cause serious delays in picking up narcotic meds containing HYDROCODONE, OXYCODONE (lortab, norco, vicodin, percocet). Your script WILL NOT be filled until the pharmacist speaks with your doctor. Be prepared to wait - you will wait however long it takes, whether its 1 hour of 6. This is not a Walgreens policy. Drop off in the morning, go to work & hope its filled by the time you get off work.
Pharmacy DRIVE THRU fact: if you think using drive thru means you receive priority or its faster, you are sadly mistaken. Customers in the store at the counter take priority over drive thru.
Per my pain management doc 2 days ago....the Feds have tightened dispensing of narcotics even MORE. If you have a med change involving narcotics, now the DEA is notified & expect ADDITIONAL delays.

Order their highlight dish.. Xiao Long Bao aka juicy soup dumplings. Bite the top off, add some ginger, and drops of vinegar inside then eat it whole. Delicious :) The place was fully packed by 1130am, I just arrived right before the rush!!!
Ask for Chef Don for the Teppan Grill and get their Geisha Special!!!
Sashimi salad all the way & end it with the Crepe dessert. You'll leave in food bliss!

Don't listen to the one star review... Their Galbi (Korean Short Ribs) was bursting with flavor, tender, and juicy. Just like their name.. It was deeeeelicious. Very on point in taste. I had the Galbi and Bibim Naengmyeon (spicy cold noodles)  combo... Enjoyed all of it. Happy tummy :) Soondubu (spicy soft tofu stew) had a great kick.. so good! And Al Chigae (spicy fish egg soup) was also quite seoulful ;)) Open late for midnight korean cravings. I approve :D

Get the Oxtail Pho! So soothing and delicious. Love the broth! Make sure they give you the sides for pho to add in. We didn't get ours until the owner noticed after getting our pho. Shaken beef was on the salty side, but was tender and flavorful. Lotus Root Salad was unique and refreshing. Make sure if all in your party orders hot tea that you request the tea pot! We all ordered hot tea, but instead of getting the tea pot we received individual tea mugs and was charged for each.
Come here for lunch. More noodles and sauce! Dinner hour not so much. Known for their Jajangmyun!
If you order the Jajangmyun.. ask for a fork. The noodles.. if given a generous portion weigh a ton!!! :P
Get the Tom Yum Shrimp. Spice level 5. Such a flavorful soup! SKIP the vermicelli pork and pad see ew!!! Their soup is the only thing I will get!
Tom Yum Shrimp!!! Stick to this soup!!!

One of my favorite spots for Vietnamese comfort food. Love their Banh Khot (mimi savory pancakes w\/ shrimp), Pho Dac Biet (combination of everything), and what they are known for... having authentic Bun Cha Ha Noi.

Order their Kimchi Noodle Soup if you love spicy. The flavor is amazingly clean. Their Fried Pork Spring Rolls is one of the best I've had. Tons of meat and they use rice paper instead of the thick egg roll wrapping. Crispy, light yet juicy inside. Love! Don't forget those Pork Chops!!! Also one of my favorites here ;)
Aim for the desserts crepes! LouLou was such a delight. I tried their galettes, but felt like I was tasting air.. no flavor.
Love their Jasmine Milk Tea and Latte

Do NOT get the Tiramisu. It's a one bite wonder.. like you wonder why you ordered it!!! It also looks nothing like a Tiramisu, but a tiny rectangular dry, tasteless pound cake. Try their Green Tea Panna Cotta first, before any other dessert or you won't be able to taste it!
You can opt for the Dinner Menu during lunch if your want the dinner item only selection. You'll just have to pay for the dinner price not lunch though!
